.SH "NAME"
memscan \- Find a character in an area of memory\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ *\ memscan('u
.BI "void * memscan(void\ *\ " "addr" ", int\ " "c" ", size_t\ " "size" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIaddr\fR
.RS 4
The memory area
.RE
.PP
\fIc\fR
.RS 4
The byte to search for
.RE
.PP
\fIsize\fR
.RS 4
The size of the area\&.
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
returns the address of the first occurrence of
\fIc\fR, or 1 byte past the area if
\fIc\fR
is not found
